tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated fasting glucose, total cholesterol, LDL cholesterol, and triglycerides, with low HDL cholesterol, indicating poorly controlled dyslipidemia and impaired glucose metabolism, increasing cardiovascular risk. Renal function and microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend clinical follow-up for metabolic syndrome and cardiovascular risk management.
